==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seceder
<hw>Se*ced"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
secedes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of a numerous body of
Presbyterians in Scotland who seceded from the communion of the
Established Church, about the year 1733, and formed the Secession
Church, so called.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secern</ent>⟦br⟧
